replies.body:
Round three: Survivability, but has to include offensive stats. 
However the hextech gunblade benefits both so I won't list it here.

AP: {{item:3504}} {{item:3174}} {{item:3102}} {{item:3030}} {{item:3152}} {{item:3151}} {{item:3027}} {{item:3116}} {{item:3157}} 
The first two being relegated to supports, having pitiful stats despite being the only regeneration options left. The two hextech items being mutually exclusive and risky to use. Torment and crystal scepter having mediocre amounts of health and nothing more. Rod of ages often takes too long to scale up before it's useful, not to mention it encourages taking damage, in a meta where burst wins games. Hourglass has been nerfed what three times now? Like the veil it's conditionally useful.

AD: {{item:3153}} {{item:3812}} {{item:3814}} {{item:3022}} {{item:3026}} {{item:3156}} {{item:3139}} {{item:3046}} {{item:3053}} {{item:3071}} {{item:3072}} {{item:3078}} {{item:3091}} 
Again more items, and more generally useful items. Across the items; lifesteal effectively being hidden extra health in a duel, having options between multiple shielding effects, damage reduction, and flat health. Triforce would be paired with the gunblade, but riot removed the ability power, leaving only the lich bane for magic damage dealers, which has mana and movement speed.
